Class: MappableElement


Package Name:
Stereotype:
Description: 
A mappable element is any biological object that can be positioned on a map. 
This is a superclass of all mappable elements, including Vector, Map, Oligo, 
Clone, Gene, MapFeature, GeneticMarker, DNASequence, and AASequence. 
There will be more mappable element types in the second version. 
Mappable Elements that have sub-structures are maps. 2/8/00 sue

Class Type: Concrete
Class Format: class

Class: DNAFragment

Stereotype:

Class: PolymorphicState


Package Name:
Stereotype:
Description: 
A polymorphic state in TAIR is any polymorphic state of a mappable element. 
Currently, this class is for the different states of a genetic marker. 
can be sequence, visible,,,many polymorphic states can be associated with a 
single genetic marker. Polymorphic states associated with a single genetic marker 
are associated through a polymorphic state number that is the polymprphism name
and sequential number. Not all polymorphic states are genetic_markers_(e.g. alleles)-lr2.08.00

Class: PolymorphicState


Package Name:
Stereotype:
Description: 
A polymorphic state in TAIR is any polymorphic state of a mappable element. 
Currently, this class is for the different states of a genetic marker. 
can be sequence, visible,,,many polymorphic states can be associated with a 
single genetic marker. Polymorphic states associated with a single genetic marker 
are associated through a polymorphic state number that is the polymprphism name
and sequential number. Not all polymorphic states are genetic_markers_(e.g. alleles)-lr2.08.00

Class Type: Concrete
Class Format: class
Persistent Class: No
Reference Class: False
Header File:

Class: PolymorphicState


Package Name:
Stereotype:
Description: 
A polymorphic state in TAIR is any polymorphic state of a mappable element. 
Currently, this class is for the different states of a genetic marker. 
can be sequence, visible,,,many polymorphic states can be associated with a 
single genetic marker. Polymorphic states associated with a single genetic marker 
are associated through a polymorphic state number that is the polymprphism name
and sequential number. Not all polymorphic states are genetic_markers_(e.g. alleles)-lr2.08.00

Class: PolymorphicState


Package Name:
Stereotype:
Description: 
A polymorphic state in TAIR is any polymorphic state of a mappable element. 
Currently, this class is for the different states of a genetic marker. 
can be sequence, visible,,,many polymorphic states can be associated with a 
single genetic marker. Polymorphic states associated with a single genetic marker 
are associated through a polymorphic state number that is the polymprphism name
and sequential number. Not all polymorphic states are genetic_markers_(e.g. alleles)-lr2.08.00

Stereotype: Notation

NotePad:

Number:
Predefined Stereotype: Notation
User Defined Stereotype:
Note Text: 
displayChromTable:

chromosome   name   status   accNo   insertSize   seqSize   marker (pos)   overlapWithNext   overlapSize   groupName   note

This table should allow the user to insert new rows, edit data for pre-existing rows and delete rows.
The whole chromosome should be accessible by scrolling and a search box should be provided.
Ideally we would also like a button for graphically displaying the newly edited portion of the map.
The chrom column will contain the chromosome number, and should be automatically filled in.
The groupName should also be automatically provided from the login information.
Status should be selected from a popup menu.  The only required fields are chromosome,
name and status.

Stereotype: Notation

NotePad:

Number:
Predefined Stereotype: Notation
User Defined Stereotype:
Note Text: 
DisplaySummaryOfChanges

This could be in text form or even better, in graphic form.
(i.e. a picture of how the AGI map for this region would look
after the changes are implemented).

does a single clone appear in two places?
is the name nonstandard?  extra zeros to remove?
We'll add to this list in the beta-testing phase.

Arabidopsis genome. It will be associated to genes (or orfs), genetic markers, 
polymorphic states, and map features. A locus will have at least one assignment.
This class has not been implemented in the current version, but will be in the next one.

Class: PolymorphicState


Package Name:
Stereotype:
Description: 
A polymorphic state in TAIR is any polymorphic state of a mappable element. 
Currently, this class is for the different states of a genetic marker. 
can be sequence, visible,,,many polymorphic states can be associated with a 
single genetic marker. Polymorphic states associated with a single genetic marker 
are associated through a polymorphic state number that is the polymprphism name
and sequential number. Not all polymorphic states are genetic_markers_(e.g. alleles)-lr2.08.00
